<h2>3. Break down the task
</h2>

<p>Sometimes a challenge feels so big that we can sometimes become stuck as we’re so focused on trying to do that one thing that we can’t do anything else.
</p>

<p>When that happens, it can be helpful to find a task that we can do.
</p>

<p>If you have a list of things to do, aim to complete the first one.
</p>

<p>If the tasks is to read or write several pages, aim for one page, or one paragraph.
</p>

<p>When we set ourselves a small goal that we know we can do, it can give us the motivation to do more (and if we don’t, we’ve still met our goal).
</p>

<p>Doing something small, is better than doing nothing. Whether you go step by step, or toe by toe, you’re still moving forward.
</p>

