<h2>6. Count yourself In
</h2>

<p>It’s been shown that we need to prepare ourselves mentally to do certain tasks. Get ourselves into “the right mindset”. This can sometimes be very hard. One way to combat this is to dedicate a specific amount of time to preparation, based upon how long we think we need.
</p>

<p>It’s like the start of a race. We see a countdown that helps prepare athletes for the start. 3… 2… 1… Go!!
</p>

<p>Each step the athletes can prepare to start, and we can do that for ourselves for our own challenges.
</p>

<p>Finding it difficult to do a task? Count yourself in. You can even add your preparation tasks to your countdown.
</p>

<p>3…Collect all the things I need 2… See the challenge ahead, 1… I’m going to do this, and Go!!
</p>

<p>This approach is something that has helped me a lot over the years. For small tasks a simple “3-2-1 Go!” can work but for bigger challenges I might count myself in from 20, and use each countdown to take a deep breathe in and out (or more if I was particularly stressed). I could then be more calm and more focused to do the challenge ahead.
</p>

<h2>Good Luck!
</h2>

<p>I hope these tips help you get your thing done!
